<h1>Clack - Web Application Environment for Common Lisp</h1>

<p><a href="https://travis-ci.org/fukamachi/clack" ><img src="https://travis-ci.org/fukamachi/clack.svg?branch=master" alt="Build Status" /></a>
<a href="https://coveralls.io/r/fukamachi/clack" ><img src="https://coveralls.io/repos/fukamachi/clack/badge.svg?branch=master" alt="Coverage Status" /></a></p>

<p>Clack is a web application environment for Common Lisp inspired by Python&apos;s WSGI and Ruby&apos;s Rack. Your awesome framework should base on this.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>

<pre><code><span class="code"><span class="paren1">(<span class="code"><i><span class="symbol">defpackage</span></i> simple-app
  <span class="paren2">(<span class="code"><span class="keyword">:use</span> <span class="keyword">:cl</span>
        <span class="keyword">:clack</span></span>)</span></span>)</span>
<span class="paren1">(<span class="code">in-package <span class="keyword">:simple-app</span></span>)</span>

<span class="paren1">(<span class="code"><i><span class="symbol">defvar</span></i> <span class="special">*handler*</span>
    <span class="paren2">(<span class="code">clackup
      #'<span class="paren3">(<span class="code"><i><span class="symbol">lambda</span></i> <span class="paren4">(<span class="code">env</span>)</span>
          '<span class="paren4">(<span class="code">200 <span class="paren5">(<span class="code"><span class="keyword">:content-type</span> <span class="string">"text/plain"</span></span>)</span> <span class="paren5">(<span class="code"><span class="string">"Hello, Clack!"</span></span>)</span></span>)</span></span>)</span></span>)</span></span>)</span></span></code></pre>

<p>Open your web browser and go to <a href="http://localhost:5000/" >http://localhost:5000/</a>. You should get &ldquo;Hello, Clack!&rdquo;.</p>

<p>To stop the server, use <code>(clack:stop *handler*)</code>.</p>

<h2>Installation</h2>

<pre><code><span class="code"><span class="paren1">(<span class="code">ql:quickload <span class="keyword">:clack</span></span>)</span></span></code></pre>

